Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveA youth leader of the ruling APGA in Anambra has been kidnapped, killed, ad his remains dumped in Utuh, far from his hometown Ukpor Nnewi he was kidnapped from two days ago
Anambra State Police Command spokesperson, DSP Toochukwu Ikenga confirmed that a corpse was discovered in the area on Saturday, but was unable to ascertain the identity of the corpse.
“When our operatives got to the scene, the corpse had been removed by some persons, we are yet to identify, and we have also ascertained that the corpse is that of the youth leader,” he said.
Ukpor has remained one of the killing fields in the state.
LGA headquarters, police installations have been attacked on occasions in the town.
Gov Charles Soludo has been flailing in the morass of insecurity created by hoods referred to as ‘unknown gunmen” since his administration began months ago.
